spanGrp.span: Asaraf, he is a man from long ago
We have heard our grandfather and grandmother tell us that he was tall, really tall.
049-001 Asaraf ga ipi natam̃ol ni teetwei § 049-002 Go komam unrogo kin apu me
ati nigmam ruto nigmam trausi na ipi natam̃ol nen ipram , ipram kotkot .
When he wanted to go, he was there and he wanted to go to Erromango.
§ 049-003 Malnen ina kefak , itu sa imur na kefak Ermag .
When he crossed the sea to Erromango, the sea came to his knee.
§ 049-004 Malnen isiwer ur ntas kin ipak Ermag , go ntas ipam̃or nap̃utuen .
He went to Erromango and he came back, and one day, well, Erromango it was-, you could be on Efate and you could see Erromango.
§ 049-006 Me ina ipak Ermag pan kaimer ler mai go naliati iskei welkia Ermag , ipi , kutae to Efat go kuto lek Ermag .
But the one from Erromango, [correction] the one from Efate made him angry.
And he really moved Erromango, he planted his head in the sea like this.
§ 049-008 Me , teni , teni Ermag , teni Efat rupregi imaet § 049-009 Go itrau to
nrus ki Ermag ipak inrus pa , me welkia ina ilao ki np̃aun pak ntas tefla .
He did that with (his head) and the sea rose.
§ 049-010 Me ipregi teflan ki nana go ntas ipo puk .
Well, he put his head in the water and he twisted his head like this so that the water rose.
§ 049-011 Welkia , ipreg na p̃aun pak ntas tefla me ipulki np̃aun tefla , nen kin ntas ina ifuk .
And then you couldn't see Erromango.
And now that he stayed there, he stayed on Efate until the time that he died, and the old people of that place buried him.
But because he was so tall, they bent him in three.
§ 049-013 Go malnen kin itu san to , itu Efat toto panpan malnen kin imat ,
go tiawi ni esan rupo § 049-014 Me nlaken ipram top go rupo p̃elkin itolwes .
